The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Monday, September 19, 2005 

 IN THE CITY

 East Bengal have been fined Rs 3 lakh over the John Dias fiasco. The India midfielder, who decided to play for Dempo SC after practising with East Bengal for about a month, also has to cough up a fine of Rs 1 lakh. 

 Both East Bengal and Dias could approach the Appeals Committee against the decision within seven days.

 Dias? signature in the East Bengal?s contract form, which the former Salgaocar player claimed to have been forged, would be sent for forensic examination.

 Meanwhile, Das Munshi said the next coach would be an Indian and the federation is looking for a foreign technical director. 

 Joy Creators beat Labvantage to move into the semi-finals of Gold Plate category in the Corporate Indoor cricket meet at Space Circle on Sunday. In another quarter final match, DPSC defeated Grasim Ultra Tech. 

 CRICKET: Indoor meet at Space Circle from 7 pm.




